/web.archive.org/web/20130618022847/http://www.billboard.com/artist/280012/soundtrack/chart?f=337|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|4\n|}\n\nAn additional album featuring [[John Powell (composer)|John Powell]]'s original score was released on April 8, 2014 by [[Sony Classical]].<ref>{{cite press release|title=Original Motion Picture Score Soundtrack Of RIO 2 Available April 8|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/original-motion-picture-score-soundtrack-of-rio-2-available-april-8-250120321.html|publisher=PR Newswire|accessdate=March 26, 2014|author=Sony Classical|date=March 13, 2014|archivedate=March 27, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140327203925/http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/original-motion-picture-score-soundtrack-of-rio-2-available-april-8-250120321.html|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Future==\n===Possible Sequel===\nDirector [[Carlos Saldanha]] has kept the possibility for ''Rio 3'' open. He has stated, \"Of course, I have a lot of stories to tell, so we're [starting to] prepare for it.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Rio 3: The Cast Tells Us Where They Want to Go In A Sequel|publisher=Cinemablend.com|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/new/Rio-3-Cast-Tells-Us-Where-They-Want-Go-Sequel-42545.html|accessdate=April 14, 2014|date=April 14, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140415144913/http://www.cinemablend.com/new/Rio-3-Cast-Tells-Us-Where-They-Want-Go-Sequel-42545.html|archivedate=April 15, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n===Spin-off===\nOn October 25, 2019, after the [[acquisition of 21st Century Fox by Disney]], it was announced that a spin-off centered on Nico and Pedro was in development for [[Disney+]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://discussingfilm.net/2019/10/25/ice-age-rio-spinoffs-in-early-development-for-disney-exclusive/|title=Ice Age and Rio spinoffs in early development for Disney+|work=Discussing Film|date=October 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n*{{Official website|http://www.rio-themovie.com}}\n* {{IMDb title|2357291|Rio 2}}\n* {{mojo title|rio2|Rio 2}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|Rio_2|Rio 2}}\n* {{metacritic film|rio-2|Rio 2}}\n\n{{Blue Sky Studios}}\n{{Portal bar|Cartoon}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rio 2}}\n[[Category:2014 films]]\n[[Category:2014 3D films]]\n[[Category:2014 computer-animated films]]\n[[Category:2010s adventure films]]\n[[Category:2010s American animated films]]\n[[Category:2010s children's comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s children's animated films]]\n[[Category:2010s fantasy films]]\n[[Category:2010s musical films]]\n[[Category:American children's animated adventure films]]\n[[Category:American children's animated comedy films]]\n[[Category:American children's animated fantasy films]]\n[[Category:American computer-animated films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American musical films]]\n[[Category:2010s sequel films]]\n[[Category:American sequel films]]\n[[Category:Animated adventure films]]\n[[Category:Animated comedy films]]\n[[Category:Animated musical films]]\n[[Category:Animated films about birds]]\n[[Category:2010s children's fantasy films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Blue Sky Studios films]]\n[[Category:Fictional parrots]]\n[[Category:Films scored by John Powell]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Carlos Saldanha]]\n[[Category:Films featuring anthropomorphic characters]]\n[[Category:Films set in Brazil]]\n[[Category:Films set in jungles]]\n[[Category:Films set in Rio de Janeiro (city)]]\n[[Category:Films set in South America]]\n[[Category:3D animated films]]\n[[Category:20th Century Fox films]]\n[[Category:20th Century Fox animated films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2014 US animated film directed by Carlos Saldanha}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2014}}\n{{Infobox film\n|name           = Rio 2\n|image          = Rio 2 Poster.JPG\n|border         = yes\n|alt            = A group of blue birds sitting on the head of a crocodile, that is submerged in a river\n|caption        = Theatrical release poster\n|director       = [[Carlos Saldanha]]\n|producer       = Bruce Anderson<br />John C. Donkin\n|screenplay     = {{Plainlist |\n* [[Don Rhymer]]\n* Carlos Kotkin\n* [[Jenny Bicks]]\n* Yoni Brenner\n}}\n|story          = Carlos Saldanha\n|based on       = {{Plainlist | \n* Characters by \n* Carlos Saldanha \n* Earl Richey Jones \n* Todd Jones\n}}\n|starring       = {{plainlist |\n* [[Jesse Eisenberg]]\n* [[Anne Hathaway]]\n* [[George Lopez]]\n* [[Jemaine Clement]]\n* [[Kristin Chenoweth]]\n* [[Andy Garc\u00eda]]\n* [[Bruno Mars]]\n* [[Leslie Mann]]\n* [[Rodrigo Santoro]]\n* [[Rachel Crow]]\n* [[Amandla Stenberg]]\n* [[Pierce Gagnon]]\n* [[Rita Moreno]]\n* [[Miguel Ferrer]]\n* [[Tracy Morgan]]\n* [[will.i.am]]\n* [[Jamie Foxx]]\n}}\n|music          = [[John Powell (film composer)|John Powell]]\n|cinematography = Renato Falc\u00e3o\n|editing        = Harry Hitner\n|studio         = {{plainlist|\n* [[Blue Sky Studios]]\n* [[20th Century Fox Animation]]\n}}\n|distributor    = [[20th Century Fox]]\n|released       = {{Film date|2014|03|20|International|2014|04|11|United States}}\n|runtime        = 101 minutes<!--Theatrical runtime: 101:06--><ref name=BBFC>{{cite web|title=''RIO 2'' (U)|url=https://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/rio-2-film-0|work=[[20th Century Fox]]|publisher=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|date=March 5, 2014|accessdate=March 5, 2014}}</ref>\n|country        = United States \n|language       = English<ref name=BBFC/>\n|budget         = $103 million<ref>{{cite web|last=Faughnder|first=Ryan|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/cotown/la-et-ct-can-captain-america-coast-over-rio-2-20140409,0,3427483.story|title='Rio 2' to take on 'Captain America: The Winter Soldier' at box office|publisher=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=April 10, 2014|accessdate=April 11, 2014|url-status=live|archivedate=June 30, 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090630013226/http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/cotown/la-et-ct-can-captain-america-coast-over-rio-2-20140409,0,3427483.story|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n|gross          = $498.8 million<ref name=mojo>{{cite web|title=Rio 2 (2014)|url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=rio2.htm|publisher=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=November 10, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Rio 2''''' is a 2014 American [[3D film|3D]] [[Computer-animated film|computer-animated]] [[Musical film|musical]] [[comedy film]] produced by [[Blue Sky Studios]] and directed by [[Carlos Saldanha]]. It is the sequel to the 2011 [[computer-animated]] film ''[[Rio (2011 film)|Rio]]'' and the studio's first film since [[Ice Age (2002 film)|''Ice Age'']] to have a sequel. The title refers to the Brazilian city of [[Rio de Janeiro (city)|Rio de Janeiro]], where the first film was set and ''Rio 2'' begins, though most of its plot occurs in the [[Amazon rainforest]]. Featuring the returning voices of [[Jesse Eisenberg]], [[Anne Hathaway]], [[will.i.am]], [[Jamie Foxx]], [[George Lopez]], [[Tracy Morgan]], [[Jemaine Clement]], [[Leslie Mann]], [[Rodrigo Santoro]], and [[Jake T. Austin]], with new members including [[Bruno Mars]], [[Andy Garcia]], [[Rita Moreno]], [[Rachel Crow]], [[Kristin Chenoweth]], [[Amandla Stenberg]], [[Pierce Gagnon]], and [[Miguel Ferrer]], the film was released internationally on March 20, 2014,<ref name=Cast /> and on April 11, 2014,<ref name=\"Cast\" /> in American theaters. The film grossed $498 million worldwide and received mixed reviews from critics, with praise for the animation, visuals, and music, but criticism for its story and writing.\n==Plot==\n[[Spix's Macaw]]s Blu and Jewel and their three children\u2014Bia, Carla, and Tiago\u2014are living happily [[Rio de Janeiro|in the city]] but Jewel is disappointed to see her children becoming too domesticated like their father. Meanwhile, Blu's former owner, Linda Gunderson and her [[Ornithology|ornithologist]] husband, Tulio are on an expedition in the [[Amazon rainforest|Amazon]] and, after a fall down a waterfall, discover a quick-flying Spix's macaw that loses one of its feathers. When word gets out about this through television, Jewel believes that they should go to the Amazon to help find the blue macaws. While the kids are ecstatic, Blu is uncertain, but he is pressured into going along. Blu brings a [[fanny pack]] full of supplies, including a [[Global Positioning System|GPS]], much to Jewel's chagrin.\n\nMeanwhile, the leader of a group in a line of [[illegal logging]] named Big Boss, discovers Linda and Tulio's expedition to find the macaws and orders his henchmen to hunt them down to avoid disruptions to their work. At the same time, the evil cockatoo Nigel seeks revenge against Blu for crippling his ability to fly, and makes several failed attempts to kill Blu along with his new lackeys, an anteater named Charlie and a poisonous frog named Gabi, who is in love with Nigel. Blu, his family, and their friends, Rafael the toucan, Pedro the cardinal, and Nico the canary, use a boat to get to the jungle. When they arrive, they initially find nothing. However, they are eventually taken to a flock of blue macaws that are hiding in an uncharted section of the Amazon. There, they meet Jewel's stern long-lost father, Eduardo, his older sister Mimi, and Jewel's childhood friend and old flame, Roberto. Eduardo seems unimpressed with Blu, but expresses gratitude to him over bringing Jewel back home. Having lost their previous habitat to arson from the illegal loggers, Eduardo is incredibly anti-human, and angrily brushes off Blu's suggestion to expose the sanctuary to Linda and Tulio to ensure their protection. At the same time, Blu is intimidated by the suave Roberto, who quickly bonds with Blu's kids.\n\nWhile searching for the macaws, Linda and Tulio are eventually captured by the loggers. Meanwhile, Blu does his best to fit in with the flock, as his family are doing, but his continued reliance on human tools prevent him from connecting with anyone. Meanwhile, in another attempt to get closer to Blu, Nigel successfully wins a talent show to become a performer for a Carnival show that Rafael, Pedro, Nico and Blu's daughter Carla are hosting. When Blu tries to pick a Brazilian nut for Jewel, he accidentally tries to get it in the territory of the Spix macaw's enemies, the [[scarlet macaw]]s, led by the hostile Felipe. Blu inadvertently causes war between the two tribes for food when he accidentally swats Felipe with a branch. The war turns out to be just like football (soccer), and Blu accidentally costs the flock their territory when he scores into [[own goal]]. Blu flies off, upset over his failures despite his best intentions and efforts.\n\nRegardless of the difficulties, Blu decides that he will leave his human roots behind him if it means building a future with his family. He visits Linda and Tulio's campsite to drop off his fanny pack, but discovers that it had been raided. Roberto accuses Blu of betraying the flock, but before Blu can defend himself, loggers storm the area. Roberto, unable to deal with real danger, panics and Blu is forced to save him from an oncoming bulldozer. Blu immediately steps up and orders Roberto to warn the flock while he goes to rescue Linda and Tulio. After doing so, Blu persuades the macaws to defend their homes instead of running away. With Blu's knowledge of human technology and help from the scarlet macaws, they're able to successfully disable the loggers' machinery. Big Boss tries to blow up the trees instead, but Blu steals the lit dynamite and takes it into the sky where it detonates harmlessly. Big Boss runs off before Linda and Tulio can stop him, but winds up getting eaten by a [[boa constrictor]]. Nigel then attacks Blu in a final attempt to get revenge, but Gabi, while attempting to help, accidentally hits Nigel with one of Charlie's pines filled with her poison; Nigel gives a theatrical death speech before seemingly dying, and Gabi then drinks her own poison to die alongside Nigel. However, it's revealed that Gabi isn't poisonous at all, and an overjoyed Gabi lovingly smothers a dismayed Nigel and drags him away.   \n\nWith the flock now under Linda and Tulio's protection, Blu and Jewel decide to live in the Amazon with their kids, though still agreeing to visit Rio in the summer. Eduardo finally drops his anti-human stance by wearing a fannypack of his own, and proudly accepts Blu into the flock. Nigel and Gabi are sent to Rio for study, Nico and Pedro's Carnival show goes on, and Luiz the bulldog arrives at the Amazon for a visit.\n\n==Voice cast==\n[[File:Anne Hathaway 2014 (cropped).jpg|thumb|[[Anne Hathaway]] at the film's screening at [[Nickelodeon Studios]] in [[Burbank, California]] on April 26, 2014]]\n\n<!-- MAIN CAST AS IDENTIFIED IN FILM CREDITS AND IN CREDIT ORDER -->\n* [[Anne Hathaway]] as Jewel, a female [[Spix's macaw]] from Rio de Janeiro and Blu's mate<ref name=Cast/>\n* [[Jesse Eisenberg]] as Blu, a male Spix's macaw from [[Moose Lake, Minnesota|Moose Lake]] who was born in Rio de Janeiro and Jewel's mate<ref name=Cast>{{cite news|title=Twentieth Century Fox Animation Announces RIO 2 Casting|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20130222005613/en/Twentieth-Century-Fox-Animation-Announces-RIO-2|accessdate=February 28, 2013|newspaper=Business Wire|date=February 22, 2013|author=20th Century Fox Film|archivedate=June 30, 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090630013226/http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20130222005613/en/Twentieth-Century-Fox-Animation-Announces-RIO-2|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* [[Jemaine Clement]] as Nigel, a sadistic [[sulphur-crested cockatoo]] who seeks revenge on Blu for crippling his ability to fly<ref name=Cast/>\n* [[Kristin Chenoweth]]<ref name=Cast/> as Gabi, a [[poison dart frog]] and Nigel's sidekick<ref name=\"USA Today\"/>\n* [[will.i.am]] as Pedro, a rapping [[red-crested cardinal]]<ref name=Cast/>\n* [[George Lopez]] as Rafael, a romantic [[toco toucan]] fond of the [[Rio Carnival]], Eva's mate<ref name=Cast/>\n* [[Bruno Mars]]<ref name=Cast/> as Roberto, Jewel's suave childhood friend<ref name=\"USA Today\"/>\n* [[Leslie Mann]] as Linda, an American woman who adopted Blu for 15 years and Tulio's wife.<ref name=Cast/>\n* [[Rodrigo Santoro]] as Tulio, a Brazilian ornithologist and Linda's husband<ref name=Cast/>\n* [[Rita Moreno]] as Aunt Mimi, Eduardo's older sister and Jewel's aunt<ref name=Cast/><ref>{{cite web|title=Characters - Mimi|url=http://www.riomovies.com/characters/mimi|publisher=Rio Movies|accessdate=December 12, 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Tracy Morgan]] as Luiz, a [[bulldog]] and a chainsaw expert with a drooling condition<ref name=Cast/>\n* [[Jake T. Austin]] as Fernando, Linda and Tulio's adopted son<ref name=Cast/>\n* [[Andy Garcia]]<ref name=Cast/> as Eduardo, Jewel's father<ref name=\"USA Today\"/>\n* [[Jamie Foxx]] as Nico, a smooth and charismatic [[yellow canary]] that wears a bottle-cap hat, close friend to Pedro<ref name=Cast/>\n* [[Rachel Crow]] as Carla, Blu and Jewel's music-loving, older daughter<ref name=Cast/><ref name=\"USA Today\">{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2013/09/24/rio-2-first-look/2829083/|title=First Look: Rio 2|first=Bryan|last=Alexander|newspaper=USA Today|date=September 24, 2013|accessdate=September 24, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Crow|first=Rachel|title=#bignews It's official! I've joined the cast of RIO 2! I'll be playing the daughter macaw of Jesse Eisenberg and Anne Hathaway! #Rio2|url=https://twitter.com/iamrachelcrow/status/305013668502982656|accessdate=February 23, 2013|publisher=Twitter|date=February 22, 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Pierce Gagnon]]<ref name=Cast/> as Tiago, Blu and Jewel's youngest, mischievous, and only son<ref name=\"USA Today\"/>\n* [[Amandla Stenberg]]<ref name=Cast/> as Bia, Blu and Jewel's intelligent, younger daughter<ref name=\"USA Today\"/>\n* [[Miguel Ferrer]] as Big Boss, the head of the illegal logging activity.\n* [[Janelle Mon\u00e1e]] as Dr. Monae, a veterinarian<ref name=SMMonaeDoctor>{{cite news|url=http://www.sinuousmag.com/2014/02/janelle-monae-voicing-doctor-rio-2/|title=Photo: Janelle Mon\u00e1e Voicing as the Doctor in \u2018Rio 2\u2032|date=February 21, 2014|accessdate=February 23, 2014|newspaper=Sinious Magazine|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221230640/http://www.sinuousmag.com/2014/02/janelle-monae-voicing-doctor-rio-2/|archivedate=February 21, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* [[Natalie Morales (journalist)|Natalie Morales]] as a news anchor<ref name=Cast/><ref>{{cite news|title=Natalie gets animated in \u2018Rio 2\u2019|url=http://www.today.com/video/today/53789560/#53789560|newspaper=USA Today|date=December 10, 2013|accessdate=December 12, 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090630013226/http://www.today.com/video/today/53789560/#53789560|archivedate=June 30, 2009|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Guess who has a cameo in \"Rio 2\"? That's our very own @NMoralesNBC! pic.twitter.com/g3zk5FVSJh|url=https://twitter.com/TODAYshow/status/410416770105630721|publisher=Twitter|accessdate=December 13, 2013|author=TODAYshow|date=December 10, 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Bebel Gilberto]] as Eva, a [[keel-billed toucan]] and Rafael's mate<ref name=Cast/>\n* Philip Lawrence as Felipe, a male [[scarlet macaw]] and the hostile leader of a tribe who has a rivalry and territorial dispute with the Spix's macaws<ref>{{cite web|title=Rio 2 Interview - Bruno Mars & Philip Lawrence|url=http://www.traileraddict.com/rio-2/interview-bruno-mars-and-philip-lawrence|publisher=Trailer Addict|accessdate=March 24, 2014|author=20th Century Fox|date=March 17, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\nOn January 25, 2012, while speaking to the [[Associated Press]], S\u00e9rgio Mendes who co-wrote a song for the first film spoke about the sequel, saying: \"I think the plan is for the movie to come three or four months before the World Cup. Fox has been talking about (it) and it looks like it's going to happen. We're going to have a meeting I think next week and Carlos is coming to town to tell us the story, and it looks like it's a go.\"<ref name=\"EW2012\">{{cite news|last=Collis|first=Clark|title=Sergio Mendes says a 'Rio' sequel 'looks like it's going to happen'|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2012/01/25/rio-sequel|accessdate=March 12, 2012|newspaper=Entertainment Weekly|date=January 25, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131217040153/http://insidemovies.ew.com/2012/01/25/rio-sequel|archivedate=December 17, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In April 2012, ''[[Deadline Hollywood]]'' reported that [[Jesse Eisenberg]] had signed up to reprise his role as Blu,<ref>{{cite news|last=Finke|first=Nikki|title=Jesse Eisenberg is leaving ICM for CAA|url=https://www.deadline.com/2012/04/jesse-eisenberg-is-leaving-icm-for-caa|accessdate=April 7, 2012|newspaper=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 6, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120408190301/http://www.deadline.com/2012/04/jesse-eisenberg-is-leaving-icm-for-caa|archivedate=April 8, 2012|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and [[Anne Hathaway]] had also signed on to reprise her role as Jewel.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.flickeringmyth.com/2012/09/catwoman-joining-thor-on-spielbergs.html|title=Catwoman joining Thor on Spielberg's Robopocalypse?|accessdate=September 25, 2012|newspaper=Flickering Myth|date=September 25, 2012|archivedate=January 23, 2013|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130123120823/http://www.flickeringmyth.com/2012/09/catwoman-joining-thor-on-spielbergs.html|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In October 2012, ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' stated that Carlos Saldanha had officially signed a five-year deal with [[20th Century Fox]] that allows him to helm live-action and/or animated films, with the sequel being part of that contractual agreement.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kroll|first=Justin|title='Rio' helmer Carlos Saldanha inks Fox pact|url=https://variety.com/2012/film/news/rio-helmer-carlos-saldanha-inks-fox-pact-1118061241/|accessdate=October 26, 2012|newspaper=Variety|date=October 25, 2012|archivedate=July 31, 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130731141016/http://variety.com/2012/film/news/rio-helmer-carlos-saldanha-inks-fox-pact-1118061241/|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[Don Rhymer]], screenplay writer of the first film, died on November 28, 2012 during the writing phase of the sequel, from [[head and neck cancer]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Screenwriter Don Rhymer dies at 51|date=December 3, 2012|accessdate=February 21, 2014|url=https://variety.com/2012/film/news/screenwriter-don-rhymer-dies-at-51-1118063010/|newspaper=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413021539/http://variety.com/2012/film/news/screenwriter-don-rhymer-dies-at-51-1118063010/|archivedate=April 13, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In January 2013, [[Rodrigo Santoro]] confirmed his return to voice ornithologist Tulio Monteiro, as well as hinting that the sequel's setting will involve the [[Amazon rainforest|Amazon]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Trumbore|first=Dave|title=Rodrigo Santoro Talks 300: Rise of an Empire, Rio 2, Heleno and More|url=https://collider.com/rodrigo-santoro-senna-300-rise-of-an-empire-interview/222104/|accessdate=January 9, 2013|newspaper=Collider.com|date=January 7, 2013|archivedate=January 11, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130111013704/http://collider.com/rodrigo-santoro-senna-300-rise-of-an-empire-interview/222104/|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> 20th Century Fox and Blue Sky unveiled the first teaser trailer at the annual Las Vegas, Nevada CinemaCon on April 18, 2013.<ref>{{cite news|last=Lesnick|first=Silas|title=20th Century Fox Previews Its 2013 Slate|accessdate=April 25, 2013|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/news/cinemaconnews.php?id=103174|work=Comingsoon.net|date=September 29, 2013|archivedate=September 29, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929190240/http://collider.com/rodrigo-santoro-senna-300-rise-of-an-empire-interview/222104/|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On May 14, 2013, that same [[teaser trailer|trailer]] was released online worldwide, and attached with ''[[Epic (2013 film)|Epic]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Jardine|first=William|title=Watch: Portuguese Teaser for Rio 2|date=May 14, 2013|accessdate=May 15, 2013|url=http://www.a113animation.com/2013/05/watch-spanish-teaser-for-rio-2.html|newspaper=A113Animation|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130619133828/http://www.a113animation.com/2013/05/watch-spanish-teaser-for-rio-2.html|archivedate=June 19, 2013|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Entertainer [[Bruno Mars]] joined the cast as Roberto after director Carlos Saldanha caught his performance on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''. During production, Mars offered his own personal touches that better shaped his character's physical appearance, personality, and voice.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bruno Mars Cast In Rio 2|url=http://www.inquisitr.com/1135815/bruno-mars-cast-in-rio-2/|accessdate=February 19, 2014|work=Inquisitr.com|date=February 16, 2014|archivedate=February 25, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140225201734/http://www.inquisitr.com/1135815/bruno-mars-cast-in-rio-2/|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n[[File:Rodrigo Santoro, Sergio Mendes, Rio 2 press junket.jpg|thumb|[[Rodrigo Santoro]], who voices Tulio, and the soundtrack's producer [[S\u00e9rgio Mendes]] at the film's press event.]]\nThe film was released to international theaters on March 20, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|author=Nancy Tartaglione|url=https://www.deadline.com/2014/04/intl-box-office-rio-2-soars-with-63-4m-weekend-captain-america-the-winter-soldier-blasts-past-300m-overseas-noah-adds-36-2m-divergent-nears-50m/|title=UPDATE: Intl Box Office: 'Rio 2' Soars With $63.4M; 'Captain America: The Winter Soldier' Blasts Past $300M Overseas; 'Noah' Adds $36.2M; 'Divergent' Nearing $50M|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=April 15, 2014|accessdate=June 14, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140520142531/http://www.deadline.com/2014/04/intl-box-office-rio-2-soars-with-63-4m-weekend-captain-america-the-winter-soldier-blasts-past-300m-overseas-noah-adds-36-2m-divergent-nears-50m/|url-status=live|archivedate=May 20, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The film's premiere was held in [[Miami, Florida]] on March 20, 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2586656/Shes-looking-Rio-nice-Anne-Hathaway-stuns-exotic-purple-orange-ensemble-sequels-premiere-Miami.html|last=Rendon|first=Christine|title=Anne Hathaway stuns in purple and orange ensemble at Rio 2 premiere|publisher=Daily Mail|work=Mail Online|date=March 22, 2014|accessdate=June 14, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20140615101445/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2586656/Shes-looking-Rio-nice-Anne-Hathaway-stuns-exotic-purple-orange-ensemble-sequels-premiere-Miami.html|archivedate=June 15, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The film was released theatrically in the United States on April 11, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deadline.com/2013/12/rio-2-trailer-movie-video/|title=[VIDEO&#93; 'Rio 2' New Trailer - Release Date April 11, 2014|website=Deadline Hollywood|date= December 12, 2013|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Marketing===\nUnder the supervision of 20th Century Fox\u2014with director [[Carlos Saldanha]] and music composer [[John Powell (composer)|John Powell]]\u2014the film's natural hometown of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil used the film as a tie-in promotion for the 2014 [[New Year's Eve]] celebration at [[Copacabana Beach]].<ref>{{cite web|title=New Year\u2019s Eve in Copacabana 2014 there will be the animation \"Rio 2\" as the theme|publisher=Rentamar|url=http://rentamar.com.br/blog/new-years-eve-in-copacabana-2014-there-will-be-the-animation-rio-2-as-the-theme-3|accessdate=February 21, 2014|date=December 27, 2013}}</ref>\n\nThree of four ''[[Angry Birds Rio]]'' episodes \u2014 all visually tied to ''Rio 2'' \u2014 have been released.<ref>{{cite web|title=New Angry Birds Rio Rocket Rumble Update Out Now!|url=http://www.angrybirdsnest.com/angry-birds-rio-rocket-rumble-update/|publisher=Angry Birds Nest|accessdate=April 17, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140326070737/http://www.angrybirdsnest.com/angry-birds-rio-rocket-rumble-update/|archivedate=March 26, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The first, \"Rocket Rumble\", was released in December 2013,<ref>{{cite press release|title=The Gang from \"RIO\" is Going for the \"Angry Birds\"|accessdate=April 17, 2014|date=December 18, 2014|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20131218005336/en/Gang-%E2%80%9CRIO%E2%80%9D-%E2%80%9CAngry-Birds%E2%80%9D|publisher=Business Wire|archivedate=April 19, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419112225/http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20131218005336/en/Gang-%E2%80%9CRIO%E2%80%9D-%E2%80%9CAngry-Birds%E2%80%9D|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> the second, \"High Dive\", in February 2014,<ref>{{cite web|title=Take a High Dive in Angry Birds Rio and Set the River Dolphins Free!|url=http://www.rovio.com/en/news/blog/468/take-a-high-dive-in-angry-birds-rio-and-set-the-river-dolphins-free/|publisher=[[Rovio Entertainment|Rovio]]|accessdate=March 23, 2014|date=February 20, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413020550/http://www.rovio.com/en/news/blog/468/take-a-high-dive-in-angry-birds-rio-and-set-the-river-dolphins-free/|archivedate=April 13, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and the third, \"Blossom River\", in April 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jump on a Riverboat for a Crazy Cruise in Angry Birds Rio!/|publisher=Rovio|accessdate=April 17, 2014|url=http://www.rovio.com/en/news/blog/487/jump-on-a-riverboat-for-a-crazy-cruise-in-angry-birds-rio|date=April 10, 2014|archivedate=April 19, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419025935/http://www.rovio.com/en/news/blog/487/jump-on-a-riverboat-for-a-crazy-cruise-in-angry-birds-rio|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In April 2014, [[Kohl's]] began selling Blu, Gabi, and Luiz plush toys as a part of their Kohl's Cares merchandise program.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20140415005104/en/Kohl%E2%80%99s-Cares-Offers-Exclusive-RIO-2-Merchandise#.U5yMXUDH1n4|title=Kohl\u2019s Cares Offers Exclusive RIO 2 Merchandise for Just $5|publisher=Business Wire|date=April 15, 2014|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\n''Rio 2'' was released on Blu-ray (2D and 3D) and DVD on July 15, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Rio-2-Blu-ray/102855/|title=Rio 2 Blu-ray|publisher=Blu-ray.com|date=May 17, 2014|accessdate=May 28, 2014|url-status=live|archivedate=May 16, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140516232239/http://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Rio-2-Blu-ray/102855/|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The Target exclusive comes with a Blu plush toy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Rio-2-Blu-ray/99679/|title=Rio 2 Blu-ray|publisher=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=May 28, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140529085601/http://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Rio-2-Blu-ray/99679/|url-status=live|archivedate=May 29, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> A limited sing-along edition of the film was released on Blu-ray and DVD on November 4, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=Rio 2 Sing-Along Blu-ray|url=http://www.blu-ray.com/news/?id=14937|publisher=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=September 10, 2014|date=September 8, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Rio 2 Sing-Along Blu-ray|url=http://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Rio-2-Sing-Along-Blu-ray/112622/|publisher=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=September 10, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critical response===\nOn [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film has an approval rating of 48% based on 115 reviews and an average rating of 5.43/10. The site's critical consensus reads, \"Like most sequels, ''Rio 2'' takes its predecessor's basic template and tries to make it bigger -- which means it's even busier, more colorful, and ultimately more exhausting for viewers outside the youthful target demographic.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Rio 2 (2014)|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/rio_2|work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film has a score of 49 out of 100 based on 34 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/rio-2|title=Rio 2 Reviews|work=[[Metacritic]]}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"A\" on an A+ to F scale, the same grade earned by its predecessor.<ref name=\"CinemaScore\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemascore.com/|title=Home - Cinemascore|work=cinemascore.com}}</ref>\n\nMark Adams of ''[[Screen Daily]]'' said, \"As a delightfully bright and breezy bit of 3D animated entertainment ''Rio 2'' hits the sweet spot, and will no doubt be a box office hit with its blend of good-natured jungle adventure, songs and gags. The only frustrating thing is that it feels very much like a by-the-numbers sequel, lacking the verve, ebullience and left-field humour that made 2011\u2019s ''Rio'' such a surprise hit.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.screendaily.com/5070106.article|author=Mark Adams|publisher=M.screendaily.com|title=Rio 2|date=March 27, 2014|accessdate=April 11, 2014|archivedate=March 31, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331100511/http://m.screendaily.com/5070106.article|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Justin Lowe of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' said, \"This rumble in the jungle adds a colorful cast of rain-forest creatures to the franchise's infectious sense of frivolity.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Rio 2 Review|date=March 26, 2014|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movie/rio-2/review/691500|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=April 11, 2014|archivedate=April 18, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140418165630/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movie/rio-2/review/691500|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Justin Chang of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' said, \"Domestic and ecological dramas abound in this bright, noisy, overstuffed sequel to Fox's 2011 surprise hit.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=Justin Chang|date=March 26, 2014|accessdate=April 11, 2014|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/reviews/film-review-rio-2-1201148036/|title=\u2018Rio 2\u2032 Review: More Is Less in Overstuffed Sequel|publisher=Variety|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140329222927/http://variety.com/2014/film/reviews/film-review-rio-2-1201148036/|url-status=live|archivedate=March 29, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Tom Huddleston of ''[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]]'' gave the film three out of five stars, saying \"There are problems here ... but the characterisation is feisty and memorable, the song-and-dance sequences intricate and colourful, and it'll charm the socks off little people.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=Tom Huddleston|publisher=Timeout.com|title=Rio 2|url=https://www.timeout.com/london/film/rio-2|date=April 4, 2014|accessdate=April 11, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413145852/http://www.timeout.com/london/film/rio-2|archivedate=April 13, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Kyle Smith of the ''[[New York Post]]'' gave the film two and a half stars out of four, saying \"''Rio 2'' is not what I would call Amazon prime, but it's got enough silly songs and daffy critters to keep the little ones happy.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Smith|first=Kyle|url=https://nypost.com/2014/04/09/birds-of-a-feather-flock-together-in-lighthearted-rio-2/|title=Birds of a feather flock together in lighthearted \u2018Rio 2\u2032|newspaper=[[New York Post]]|date=April 9, 2014|accessdate=April 11, 2014|archivedate=April 13, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413001544/http://nypost.com/2014/04/09/birds-of-a-feather-flock-together-in-lighthearted-rio-2/|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Claudia Puig of ''[[USA Today]]'' gave the film two out of four stars, saying \"''Rio 2'' teems with colorful animated splendor and elaborate musical numbers, but its rambling, hectic, if good-hearted, story is for the birds.\"<ref>{{cite news|publisher=USA Today|date=November 22, 2013|accessdate=April 11, 2014|url= https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2014/04/10/rio-2-review/6888613/|title=Vibrant 'Rio 2' feathers its nest with too many plots}}</ref> [[Richard Corliss]] of ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' gave the film a positive review, saying \"Even when it's coarse and calculating, this is an eager entertainment machine that will keep the kids satisfied. Just don't tell them that the ''Rio'' movies are musical comedies about an avian genocide.\"<ref>{{cite news|author=Richard Corliss|url=http://time.com/57096/rio-2-movie-review/|work=TIME|accessdate=April 11, 2014|title=Rio 2 Movie Review|archivedate=April 10, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140410175902/http://time.com/57096/rio-2-movie-review/|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nElizabeth Weitzman of the ''[[New York Daily News]]'' gave the film three out of five stars, saying \"We're grading on a sliding scale here. But if ''Rio 2'' is hardly Pixar quality, it's certainly better than the average animated sequel.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv-movies/rio-2-movie-review-article-1.1750916|author=Elizabeth Weitzman|title=\u2018Rio 2,\u2019 movie review|newspaper=[[Daily News (New York)|NY Daily News]]|date=April 10, 2014|accessdate=April 11, 2014|archivedate=April 13, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413002414/http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv-movies/rio-2-movie-review-article-1.1750916|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Peter Hartlaub of the ''[[San Francisco Chronicle]]'' gave the film two out of four stars, saying \"It's like the last ''Hobbit'' movie - so much time passes between side plots that you have to jog the memory when a minor character appears again. Who's that toucan again? Is he a bad guy?\"<ref>{{cite web|title='Rio 2' review: Fun but flawed|url=http://www.sfgate.com/movies/article/Rio-2-review-Fun-but-flawed-5392380.php|author=Peter Hartlaub|publisher=SFGate|date=April 10, 2014|accessdate=April 11, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140410184250/http://www.sfgate.com/movies/article/Rio-2-review-Fun-but-flawed-5392380.php|archivedate=April 10, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Bill Goodykoontz of ''[[The Arizona Republic]]'' gave the film three out of four stars, saying \"An agreeable song-and-dance movie, a laugh here, a laugh there, pleasant but overly busy, for seemingly no real reason other than to throw a few more set pieces at the wall to see what sticks.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=Bill Goodykoontz|title=Review: 'Rio 2'|url=https://www.azcentral.com/story/entertainment/movies/2014/04/10/rio-movie-review-sequel-goodykoontz/7517195/|publisher=[[The Arizona Republic|Azcentral.com]]|work=[[The Arizona Republic]]|accessdate=April 11, 2014|date=April 10, 2014}}</ref> Jessica Herndon of the [[Associated Press]] gave the film three out of four stars, saying \"With so much going on, it's a wonder this kids' movie is only five minutes longer than the original. But for the music and brilliantly picturesque look, it's worth the 3-D ticket.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Herndon|first= Jessica|url=https://www.stltoday.com/entertainment/movies/reviews/rhythmic-rio-is-dazzling-but-overloaded/article_0589c81e-07bb-51e8-8b34-5d66e6c759ee.html|date=April 10, 2014|title= Rhythmic 'Rio 2' is dazzling but overloaded: Entertainment|newspaper=[[St. Louis Post-Dispatch]]|accessdate=April 11, 2014}}</ref> Stephanie Merry of ''[[The Washington Post]]'' gave the film two out of four stars, saying \"All in all, though, the movie feels at once too busy and too derivative. That's no easy feat, but it's also one sequel-makers probably shouldn't aspire to.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=\u2018Rio 2\u2019 movie review|author=Stephanie Merry|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/goingoutguide/movies/rio-2-movie-review/2014/04/09/2add0e2c-be6a-11e3-b195-dd0c1174052c_story.html|publisher=The Washington Post|date=April 10, 2014|accessdate=April 11, 2014}}</ref> Bruce Demara of the ''[[Toronto Star]]'' gave the film two and a half stars out of four, saying \"Those who enjoyed the adventures of Blu and Jewel and company in the first ''Rio'' are going to find the sequel an equally pleasing diversion.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=Bruce Demara|title=Rio 2 features feather-flying jungle fun: review|url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/movies/2014/04/10/rio_2_features_featherflying_jungle_fun_review.html|date=April 10, 2014|accessdate=April 11, 2014|newspaper=[[Toronto Star]]|archivedate=April 13, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413004155/http://www.thestar.com/entertainment/movies/2014/04/10/rio_2_features_featherflying_jungle_fun_review.html|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nTom Russo of ''[[The Boston Globe]]'' gave the film two out of four stars, saying \"The story flows, but not always freely, thanks to its manufactured feel.\"<ref>{{cite news|author=Tom Russo|publisher=The Boston Globe|date=April 10, 2014|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/movies/2014/04/10/rio-win-again-brazil-this-time-flying-inland/OHxHXjU2sIhVsYafL2zicN/story.html|title=\u2018Rio 2\u2019: on the win again in Brazil, this time flying inland|accessdate=April 11, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140411135638/http://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/movies/2014/04/10/rio-win-again-brazil-this-time-flying-inland/OHxHXjU2sIhVsYafL2zicN/story.html|archivedate=April 11, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Jeannette Catsoulis of ''[[The New York Times]]'' gave the film a negative review, saying \"The cinematic equivalent of attack by kaleidoscope, ''Rio 2'' sucks you in and whirls you around before spitting you out, exhausted.\"<ref>{{cite news|author=Jeannette Catsoulis|date=April 11, 2014|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/04/11/movies/rio-2-ventures-into-the-amazon-rain-forest.html?partner=rss&emc=rss&_r=0|title=Domesticated Macaws Reclaiming Their Wild Side|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|archivedate=April 17, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140417125056/http://www.nytimes.com/2014/04/11/movies/rio-2-ventures-into-the-amazon-rain-forest.html?partner=rss&emc=rss&_r=0|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Betsy Sharkey of the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' gave the film a negative review, saying \"Wonderfully animated and well-voiced, ''Rio 2'' is nevertheless too much. Too much plot, too many issues, too many characters.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/moviesnow/la-et-mn-rio-2-20140411,0,7007793.story#axzz2yVW7FcVW|last=Sharkey|first=Betsy|title=Review: Amid 'Rio 2's' cacophony, the musical numbers shine|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|date=April 10, 2014|accessdate=April 11, 2014|archivedate=April 11, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140411003343/http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/moviesnow/la-et-mn-rio-2-20140411,0,7007793.story#axzz2yVW7FcVW|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Bill Zwecker of the ''[[Chicago Sun-Times]]'' gave the film three out of four stars, saying \"It's as good as the first one and sure to please both the kiddies and adults with its two-tiered humor.\"<ref>{{cite news|author=Bill Zwecker|date=April 10, 2014|url=http://www.suntimes.com/entertainment/movies/26722552-421/rio-2-more-guffaws-from-brazils-funniest-macaws.html|title=\u2018Rio 2\u2019: More guffaws from Brazil\u2019s funniest macaws|newspaper=[[Chicago Sun-Times]]|accessdate=April 11, 2014|archivedate=April 13, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413011102/http://www.suntimes.com/entertainment/movies/26722552-421/rio-2-more-guffaws-from-brazils-funniest-macaws.html|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Tirdad Derakhshani of ''[[The Philadelphia Inquirer]]'' gave the film two out of four stars, saying \"It'll keep the kids content for a couple of hours, though it's likely to bore the grown-ups.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.philly.com/philly/entertainment/movies/20140411__Rio_2__a_gorgeous_but_muddled_sequel.html|title='Rio 2' a gorgeous but muddled sequel|work=[[The Inquirer]]|publisher=[[Philadelphia Media Network]]|date=April 11, 2014|accessdate=April 11, 2014|author=Tirdad Derakhshani|archivedate=April 13, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413011941/http://www.philly.com/philly/entertainment/movies/20140411__Rio_2__a_gorgeous_but_muddled_sequel.html|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Liam Lacey of ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'' gave the film three out of four stars, saying \"''Rio 2'' (like Fox\u2019s Ice Age series) relies on derivative plotting and slapstick visual gags, in contrast to Pixar\u2019s more cerebral originality. Where the film excels though, in an even more pronounced way than the first film, is in the choreographed animation for the musical numbers.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/try-it-now/?articleId=17925514|title=Rio 2: Thrilling, but too many bad guys|newspaper=[[The Globe and Mail]]|date=April 11, 2014|archivedate=April 12, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140412004458/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/try-it-now/?articleId=17925514|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Alonso Duralde of ''[[The Wrap]]'' gave the film a negative review, saying \"The musical moments, on the whole, stand out as the highlights of the film; ''Rio 2'' becomes watchable when the flat characters shut up and sing.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=Alonso Duralde|date=April 11, 2014|url=https://www.thewrap.com/rio-2-review-jesse-eisenberg-anne-hathaway|title=\u2018Rio 2' Review: A Zippy Musical Trapped Inside a Tedious Kiddie Movie|publisher=[[The Wrap]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413044042/http://www.thewrap.com/rio-2-review-jesse-eisenberg-anne-hathaway|archivedate=April 13, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nRafer Guzman of ''[[Newsday]]'' gave the film one and a half stars out of four, saying \"The movie has one goal: to amuse the most children with the least amount of effort.\"<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.newsday.com/entertainment/movies/rio-2-review-macaw-family-is-for-the-birds-1.7655945|title=Review: 'Rio 2'|newspaper=[[Newsday]]}}</ref> Steve Persall of the ''[[Tampa Bay Times]]'' gave the film a B+, saying \"Like its peppy predecessor, ''Rio 2'' doesn't look or sound like other animated licenses to print money. That alone is reason enough to appreciate it.\"<ref>{{cite news|author=Steve Persall, Times Movie Critic View all Articles|url=http://www.tampabay.com/things-to-do/movies/review-rio-2-is-worth-squawking-about/2174485|title=Review: 'Rio 2' is worth squawking about|newspaper=[[Tampa Bay Times]]|date=April 10, 2014|accessdate=April 13, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413140529/http://www.tampabay.com/things-to-do/movies/review-rio-2-is-worth-squawking-about/2174485|archivedate=April 13, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Kevin McFarland of ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' gave the film a C, saying \"Like the first film, ''Rio 2'' is almost oppressively bright, bombarding the screen with flashes of saturated rainforest colors and even a bird version of soccer (timed a bit too perfectly to the 2014 World Cup in Brazil).\"<ref>{{cite web|last=McFarland|first=Kevin|url=https://www.avclub.com/review/too-much-story-and-too-many-bright-colors-bring-do-203248|title=Too much story and too many bright colors bring down Rio 2|publisher=[[The A.V. Club]]|date=April 10, 2014|accessdate=April 13, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140411135207/http://www.avclub.com/review/too-much-story-and-too-many-bright-colors-bring-do-203248|archivedate=April 11, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Mike McCahill of ''[[The Guardian]]'' gave the film two out of five stars, saying \"It's hard to ascribe much art or wit to a franchise that retains the services of will.i.am as comic relief \u2013 and a thoroughly inorganic talent-show subplot feels like another attempt to groom youngsters for life in the Cowell jungle.\"<ref>{{cite news|author=Mike McCahill|title=Rio 2 review \u2013 wild beasts turned cash cows|date=April 3, 2014|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2014/apr/03/rio-2-review|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=April 13, 2014|url-status=live|archivedate=April 4, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140404104056/http://www.theguardian.com/film/2014/apr/03/rio-2-review|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Robbie Collin of ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'' gave the film two out of five stars, saying \"This jumbled sequel, which was also directed by Carlos Saldanha, loses most of what made the first film such an infectious entertainment.\"<ref>{{cite news|author=Robbie Collin|accessdate=April 13, 2014|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/10742623/Rio-2-review-a-jumbled-sequel.html|title=Rio 2, review: 'a jumbled sequel'|newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=April 3, 2014|archivedate=April 4, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140404060413/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/10742623/Rio-2-review-a-jumbled-sequel.html|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Eric Henderson of [[Slant Magazine]] gave the film one out of five stars, saying \"Though there isn't a fruit-flavored hue that isn't jammed into every single corner of screen space in ''Rio 2'', the movie has less actual nutritional value than 10 bowls of crushed Froot Loops dust. 20th Century Fox's sequel to the already dubious 2011 film would seem far too endlessly hyperventilating and self-stimulating a way to keep kids from barreling toward a spaz attack on a Saturday afternoon.\"<ref>{{cite web|date=April 8, 2014|accessdate=April 13, 2014|url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/film/review/rio-2|author=Eric Henderson|title=Rio 2: Film Review|publisher=[[Slant Magazine]]|archivedate=April 13, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413142453/http://www.slantmagazine.com/film/review/rio-2|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Box office===\n''Rio 2'' grossed $131,538,435 in North America, and $367,242,682 in other territories, for a worldwide total of $498,781,117, surpassing its predecessor.<ref name=\"mojo\"/> In North America, the film earned $12 million on its opening day,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2014/04/12/friday-box-office-rio-2-tops-captain-america-2/|author=Scott Mendelson|title=Friday Box Office: 'Rio 2' Tops 'Captain America 2'|publisher=[[Forbes]]|date=March 26, 2014|accessdate=April 13, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413020047/http://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2014/04/12/friday-box-office-rio-2-tops-captain-america-2/|archivedate=April 13, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and opened to number two in its first weekend, with $39,327,869, behind ''[[Captain America: The Winter Soldier]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=2014&wknd=15&p=.htm|title=Weekend Box Office Results for April 11-13, 2014|publisher=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=April 13, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140418135513/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=2014&wknd=15&p=.htm|archivedate=April 18, 2014|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In its second weekend, the film dropped to number three, grossing an additional $22,159,742.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=2014&wknd=16&p=.htm|title=Weekend Box Office Results for April 18-20, 2014|publisher=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=April 24, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140418194725/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=2014&wknd=16&p=.htm|archivedate=April 18, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In its third weekend, the film remained number three, grossing $13,881,457.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=May 1, 2014|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=2014&wknd=17&p=.htm|title=Weekend Box Office Results for April 25-27, 2014|archivedate=April 28, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140428150308/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=2014&wknd=17&p=.htm|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In its fourth weekend, the film dropped to number five, grossing $7,711,952.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=May 6, 2014|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=2014&wknd=18&p=.htm|title=Weekend Box Office Results for May 2-4, 2014|archivedate=May 6, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140506181917/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=2014&wknd=18&p=.htm|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Twentieth Century Fox Home Entertainment donated $100,000 to WWF to support conservation efforts in the Amazon.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldwildlife.org/pages/help-protect-the-amazon-so-macaws-and-other-wildlife-have-a-place-to-call-home|title=Help Protect the Amazon So Macaws and Other Wildlife Have a Place to Call Home|work=worldwildlife.org|accessdate=March 18, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141107102538/http://www.worldwildlife.org/pages/help-protect-the-amazon-so-macaws-and-other-wildlife-have-a-place-to-call-home|archivedate=November 7, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:95%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! colspan=\"5\" style=\"background: LightSteelBlue;\" | Awards\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Award\n! Category\n! Recipients and nominees\n! Result\n|-\n| [[British Academy Children's Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2014/childrens|title=Children's in 2014|publisher=BAFTA|accessdate=November 24, 2014}}</ref>\n| BAFTA Kids Vote \u2013 Feature Film\n|\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | [[42nd Annie Awards|Annie Awards]]<ref name=\"AnnieNoms\">{{cite web|title=42ND ANNUAL ANNIE AWARDS CATEGORIES AND NOMINEES|url=http://annieawards.org/nominees/|website=annieawards.org|accessdate=14 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141214091232/http://annieawards.org/nominees/|archivedate=December 14, 2014|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Evry|first1=Max|title=42nd Annual Annie Awards Nominations Announced|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/387671-42nd-annual-annie-awards-nominations-announced|accessdate=14 December 2014|work=Comingsoon.net|date=December 1, 2014}}</ref>\n| Outstanding Achievement, Character Design in an Animated Feature Production\n| Sang Jun Lee, Jason Sadler, and Jos\u00e9 Manuel Fern\u00e1ndez Oli\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Achievement, Storyboarding in an Animated Feature Production\n| John Hurst\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Achievement, Storyboarding in an Animated Feature Production\n| Rodrigo Perez-Castro\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Annie Award for Voice Acting in a Feature Production|Outstanding Achievement, Voice Acting in an Animated Feature Production]]\n| [[Andy Garc\u00eda]] as the voice of Eduardo\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[2015 Kids' Choice Awards|Kids' Choice Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/kids-choice-awards-nominees-2015-nominations-refresher-list-march-28-award-show-1861866|title=Kids\u2019 Choice Awards Nominees 2015: A Nominations Refresher List Before The March 28 Award Show|date=March 27, 2015|work=[[International Business Times]]|accessdate=March 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| Favorite Animated Movie\n|\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[41st People's Choice Awards|People's Choice Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.peopleschoice.com/2014/11/04/peoples-choice-awards-2015-nominees-full-list/|title=People\u2019s Choice Awards 2015: Full List Of Nominees - People's Choice|work=[[People's Choice Awards]]|accessdate=March 18, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141108093946/http://blog.peopleschoice.com/2014/11/04/peoples-choice-awards-2015-nominees-full-list/|archivedate=November 8, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n| Favorite Family Movie\n|\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Visual Effects Society Awards 2014|Visual Effects Society Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/planet-of-the-apes-leads-visual-effects-society-nominations/|title='Planet of the Apes' Leads Visual Effects Society Nominations|work=TheWrap|accessdate=March 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| [[Visual Effects Society Award for Outstanding Animation in an Animated Feature Motion Picture|Outstanding Animation in an Animated Feature Motion Picture]]\n| [[Carlos Saldanha]], Bruce Anderson, John C. Donkin, and Kirk Garfield\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Animated Character in an Animated Feature Motion Picture\n| Gabi \u2013 Jason Sadler, Ignacio Barrios, Drew Winey, and Diana Diriwaechter\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[19th Satellite Awards|Satellite Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pressacademy.com/award_cat/current-nominees/|work=[[International Press Academy]]|at=pressacademy.com|title=Satellite Awards (2014)|publisher=[[International Press Academy|IPA]]|accessdate=December 1, 2014|date=December 2, 2014}}</ref>\n| [[Satellite Award for Best Original Song|Best Original Song]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | \"What is Love\" \u2013 [[Janelle Mon\u00e1e]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[18th Hollywood Film Awards|Hollywood Film Awards]]<ref name=\"cbsn141114\">{{cite news|first=Lauren|last=Moraski|publisher=[[CBS News]]|title=Hollywood Film Awards 2014 winners |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/hollywood-film-awards-2014-winners/|date=November 14, 2014|accessdate=December 4, 2014}}</ref>\n| Hollywood Song Award\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n==Music==\n\n===Soundtrack===\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Rio 2: Music from the Motion Picture\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = Various Artists\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|2014|03|25}}\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Pop music|Pop]], [[Latin music (genre)|Latin]], [[alternative hip hop]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=39|s=7}}\n| label      = [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| producer   = [[S\u00e9rgio Mendes]], [[John Powell (film composer)|John Powell]]\n| chronology = [[Blue Sky Studios]] film soundtrack\n| prev_title = [[Epic (2013 film)|Epic]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title = [[The Peanuts Movie]]\n| next_year  = 2015\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Rio 2: Music from the Motion Picture\n | type        = Soundtrack\n | single1     = What Is Love\n | single1date = March 4, 2014\n}}\n}}\n\nA soundtrack for the film was released on March 25, 2014, by [[Atlantic Records]].<ref name=FMRSoundtrack>{{cite web|title=\u2018Rio 2\u2032 Soundtrack Details|url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2014/02/13/rio-2-soundtrack-details/|publisher=Film Music Reporter|accessdate=February 17, 2014|date=February 13, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140703055922/http://filmmusicreporter.com/2014/02/13/rio-2-soundtrack-details/|archivedate=July 3, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Rio 2 (Music From the Motion Picture)|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/rio-2-music-from-motion-picture/id826135967|publisher=[[iTunes]]|accessdate=March 23, 2014|url-status=live|archivedate=March 17, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140317124533/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/rio-2-music-from-motion-picture/id826135967|df=mdy-all}}</ref> It was promoted by the single \"What Is Love\", performed by [[Janelle Mon\u00e1e]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Rutherford|first=Kevin|title='Rio 2' Soundtrack Out March 25, Features Janelle Monae, Bruno Mars|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5923166/rio-2-soundtrack-out-march-25-features-janelle-monae-bruno-mars|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=March 10, 2014|date=March 10, 2014|archivedate=May 7, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140507181653/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5923166/rio-2-soundtrack-out-march-25-features-janelle-monae-bruno-mars|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The Barbatuques performed the song \"Beautiful Creatures\" as part of the [[2016 Summer Olympics closing ceremony|closing ceremony]] of the [[2016 Summer Olympics]] in Rio de Janeiro.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Moller|first1=Kenza|title=What Is The \"We Are Beautiful Creatures\" Song From The Closing Ceremony? It Was Cheerful|url=https://www.romper.com/p/what-is-the-we-are-beautiful-creatures-song-from-the-closing-ceremony-it-was-cheerful-16800|website=Romper|accessdate=3 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n;Track listing\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Performers\n| total_length = 39:07\n| title1 = What Is Love\n| writer1 = [[Janelle Mon\u00e1e]], [[Nate \"Rocket\" Wonder]], Roman Irvin\n| extra1 = [[Janelle Mon\u00e1e]]\n| length1 = 3:31\n| title2 = Rio Rio\n| writer2 = [[Ester Dean]], [[B.o.B]], [[Stargate (music producers)| Mikkel Storleer Erikson, Tor Erik Hermansen]]\n| note2 = featuring [[B.o.B.]]\n| extra2 = [[Ester Dean]]\n| length2 = 2:41\n| title3 = Beautiful Creatures\n| writer3 = Andre Hosoi, Renato Epstein, [[Taura Stinson]]\n| extra3 = Barbatuques, [[Andy Garc\u00eda]] and [[Rita Moreno]]\n| length3 = 2:07\n| title4 = Welcome Back\n| writer4 = [[Bruno Mars]], [[Philip Lawrence (songwriter)|Philip Lawrence]], [[John Powell]]\n| extra4 = [[Bruno Mars]]\n| length4 = 1:08\n| title5 = \u00d4 Vida\n| writer5 = [[Carlinhos Brown]], Powell, [[Sergio Mendes]], Stinson\n| extra5 = [[Carlinhos Brown]] and Nina De Freitas\n| length5 = 1:47\n| title6 = It's a Jungle Out Here\n| writer6 = Lawrence, Jean Yves \"Jeeve\" Ducornet, Michael Diskint\n| note6 = featuring [[Uakti (band)|Uakti]]; Brazilian Version\n| extra6 = [[Philip Lawrence (songwriter)|Philip Lawrence]]\n| length6 = 3:59\n| title7 = Don't Go Away\n| note7 = featuring Uakti\n| writer7 = Flavia Maia, Stinson\n| extra7 = [[Anne Hathaway]] and Flavia Maia\n| length7 = 2:38\n| title8 = Batucada Familia\n| writer8 = Brown, Mendes, Powell, [[Siedah Garrett]]\n| extra8 = Carlinhos Brown, [[Siedah Garrett]], [[Jamie Foxx]], [[Rachel Crow]], [[Amy Heidemann]], Andy Garc\u00eda, and Rita Moreno\n| length8 = 2:42\n| title9 = Poisonous Love\n| writer9 = Brown, Powell, Randy Rogel\n| extra9 = [[Kristin Chenoweth]] and [[Jemaine Clement]]\n| length9 = 3:30\n| title10 = [[I Will Survive]]\n| writer10 = [[Dino Fekaris]], [[Freddie Perren]], [[Jemaine Clement]], Yoni Brenner\n| extra10 = Jemaine Clement and Kristin Chenoweth\n| length10 = 1:51\n| title11 = Bola Viva\n| writer11 = Brown, Powell, Mendes\n| extra11 = Carlinhos Brown\n| length11 = 3:22\n| title12 = Favo De Mel \n| writer12 = Mendes, Brown, Mikael Mutti, Powell, Garrett\n| extra12 = [[Milton Nascimento]]\n| length12 = 3:08\n| title13 = It's a Jungle Out Here\n| writer13 = Lawrence, Ducornet, Diskint\n| extra13 = Philip Lawrence\n| length13 = 4:00\n| title14 = What Is Love\n| writer14 = Mon\u00e1e, Wonder, Irvin\n| extra14 = Janelle Mon\u00e1e, Anne Hathaway, [[Jesse Eisenberg]], Jamie Foxx, and Carlinhos Brown\n| length14 = 2:43\n}}\n\n===Charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Chart (2014)\n! Peak<br />position\n|-\n| US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=May 6, 2014|url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/280012/soundtrack/chart|title=Soundtrack - Chart history|publisher=Billboard|archivedate=September 17, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130917224204/http://www.billboard.com/artist/280012/soundtrack/chart|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|124\n|-\n| US Soundtracks<ref>{{cite web|title=Soundtrack - Chart history|publisher=Billboard|url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/280012/soundtrack/chart?f=337|accessdate=May 6, 2014|archivedate=June 18, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130618022847/http://www.billboard.com/artist/280012/soundtrack/chart?f=337|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|4\n|}\n\nAn additional album featuring [[John Powell (composer)|John Powell]]'s original score was released on April 8, 2014 by [[Sony Classical]].<ref>{{cite press release|title=Original Motion Picture Score Soundtrack Of RIO 2 Available April 8|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/original-motion-picture-score-soundtrack-of-rio-2-available-april-8-250120321.html|publisher=PR Newswire|accessdate=March 26, 2014|author=Sony Classical|date=March 13, 2014|archivedate=March 27, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140327203925/http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/original-motion-picture-score-soundtrack-of-rio-2-available-april-8-250120321.html|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Future==\n===Possible Sequel===\nDirector [[Carlos Saldanha]] has kept the possibility for ''Rio 3'' open. He has stated, \"Of course, I have a lot of stories to tell, so we're [starting to] prepare for it.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Rio 3: The Cast Tells Us Where They Want to Go In A Sequel|publisher=Cinemablend.com|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/new/Rio-3-Cast-Tells-Us-Where-They-Want-Go-Sequel-42545.html|accessdate=April 14, 2014|date=April 14, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140415144913/http://www.cinemablend.com/new/Rio-3-Cast-Tells-Us-Where-They-Want-Go-Sequel-42545.html|archivedate=April 15, 2014|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n===Spin-off===\nOn October 25, 2019, after the [[acquisition of 21st Century Fox by Disney]], it was announced that a spin-off centered on Nico and Pedro was in development for [[Disney+]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://discussingfilm.net/2019/10/25/ice-age-rio-spinoffs-in-early-development-for-disney-exclusive/|title=Ice Age and Rio spinoffs in early development for Disney+|work=Discussing Film|date=October 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n*{{Official website|http://www.rio-themovie.com}}\n* {{IMDb title|2357291|Rio 2}}\n* {{mojo title|rio2|Rio 2}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|Rio_2|Rio 2}}\n* {{metacritic film|rio-2|Rio 2}}\n\n{{Blue Sky Studios}}\n{{Portal bar|Cartoon}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rio 2}}\n[[Category:2014 films]]\n[