iko Obayashi}}\n{{Blue Ribbon Award for Best Newcomer}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Obayashi, Nobuhiko}}\n[[Category:Japanese film directors]]\n[[Category:1938 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Hiroshima Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Medal with Purple Ribbon]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of the Rising Sun, 4th class]]\n[[Category:Horror film directors]]\n[[Category:Persons of Cultural Merit]]\n[[Category:People from Onomichi, Hiroshima]]\n", "name_user": "MatthewHoobin", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePartial filmography:Edited citation order.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nobuhiko_Obayashi"}
{"title_page": "Kihyun", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Kihyun\n| image            = 190424 Kihyun The Fact Music Awards (3).png\n| caption          = Ki-hyun at the 2019 Fact Music Awards\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1993|11|22}}\n| birth_place      = [[Goyang]], South Korea\n| birth_name       = Yoo Ki-hyun\n| occupation       = Singer\n| background       = solo_singer\n| genre            = [[K-pop]]<!-- Solo work ONLY; you must cite other genres -->\n| instrument       = Vocals\n| years_active     = 2015\u2013present\n| label            = [[Starship Entertainment|Starship]]\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Monsta X]]}}\n| website          = {{URL|monstax-e.com/}}\n| module           = {{Infobox Korean name | child = yes\n| hangul          = {{linktext|\uc720|\uae30|\ud604}}\n| hanja           = {{linktext|\u5218|\u57fa|\u8d24}}\n| rr              = Yu Gihyeon\n| mr              = Yu Kihy\u014fn\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Yoo Ki-hyun''' ([[Hangul]]: \uc720\uae30\ud604; born November 22, 1993), better known as '''Kihyun''',  is a South Korean singer. He is a vocalist in the South Korean boy band [[Monsta X]], which debuted under [[Starship Entertainment]] in 2015 through [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s survival show, ''No.Mercy''. A known sentence is '''K of Kpop is from Kihyun'''\n\n== Personal life ==\n\n=== Early life and education ===\nKihyun was born on November 22, 1993 in [[Goyang]], South Korea. He comes from a family of four,<ref>{{cite web |title=Hello Counselor EP.385 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rYexYJ0z4WE |via=YouTube |publisher=[[KBS World (TV channel)|KBS World TV]]|accessdate=November 6, 2018}}</ref> which includes his father, mother, older brother (who lives in Japan), and himself. He is a graduate of [[Dong-ah Institute of Media and Arts]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=VLive |title=[\ubaac\ucc44\ub110][B] EP.51 \ucd5c.\ubc30.\ucc3e No. 3 |url=https://www.vlive.tv/video/28575?channelCode=FE123 |website=[[V Live (website)|V Live]] |publisher=[[Naver]]|accessdate=November 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== 2014\u20132015: Debut and career beginnings ===\nIn December 2014, Kihyun competed in [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s survival show ''\"No.Mercy\"''.<ref name=\"no mercy\">{{cite news |last1=Park |first1=Gyu-oh |title=New idol group to be born through Mnet's \u2018No.Mercy\u2019 |url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201411131802564766044_2&ACE_SEARCH=1 |accessdate=November 6, 2018 |work=[[The Korea Herald|Kpop Herald]]|date=November 13, 2014}}</ref> Along with the six other trainees, they formed a hip-hop idol group [[Monsta X]] and debuted under [[Starship Entertainment]] on May 14, 2015.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sung |first1=Jin Hee |title=Monsta X, the debut picture of the 'wild rebel street' concept topic! |url=http://the-star.co.kr/site/data/html_dir/2015/05/07/2015050701065.html |accessdate=November 6, 2018 |work=[[The Chosun Ilbo|The Star Chosun]] (in Korean) |date=May 7, 2015}}</ref> \nThrough the survival show, he also released 2 collaboration tracks, \"Pillow\", with [[Sistar]]'s [[Soyou]] and [[Giriboy]] in January 14, 2015,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Writer |first1=Staff |title='No.Mercy' Comes to an End With Seven Trainees Set To Debut As Idol Group Monsta X |url=https://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/174084/20150212/no-mercy-comes-to-an-end-with-seven-trainees-set-to-debut-as-idol-group-monsta-x.htm |accessdate=November 6, 2018 |work=KpopStarz|date=February 12, 2015}}</ref> and \"0 (Young)\", with Giriboy, [[Mad Clown]], [[Jooyoung]] and a few other remaining trainees in ''\"No.Mercy\"'' in February 4, 2015.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Yoon |first1=Hee-hee |title='No.Mercy' mission sound source release ... |url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/435878 |accessdate=November 7, 2018 |work=Ten Asia The Korea Entertainment Media (in Korean) |date=February 5, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2015, Kihyun and fellow [[Monsta X]] member [[Lee Joo-heon|Jooheon]] recorded a television soundtrack titled \"Attractive Woman\" for Korean drama ''[[Orange Marmalade]]''.<ref name=\"bntnews.co.uk\">{{cite news |last1=Ha |first1=You-bin |title=MONSTA X To Sing \u2018Orange Marmalade\u2019 OST |url=http://www.bntnews.co.uk/app/news.php?nid=20500 |accessdate=November 6, 2018 |work=BNT News |date=April 20, 2015}}</ref> In October, he also sang his first solo original soundtrack \"One More Step\" for the [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s television drama ''[[She Was Pretty]]''.<ref name=\"pretty\">{{cite news |last1=Yoon |first1=Suk Min |title=\u2018She was pretty\u2019 Choi Si Won, OST directly called. Today(21st) 10 times in the first line |url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/729366 |accessdate=November 7, 2018 |work=Ten Asia The Korea Entertainment Media (in Korean) |date=October 21, 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== 2016\u2013present: Original soundtracks ===\nKihyun appeared as a contestant on the [[King of Mask Singer]] known as \"Tell Them I\u2019m the Dragon King\" on January 3, 2016. He won the first round versus [[Apink]]'s [[Kim Nam-joo (singer)|Namjoo]] known as \"Good Daughter Shim Cheong\". Unfortunately, on the second round of the competition, he lost to [[Lim Jeong-hee]] known as \"Rolled Good Fortune\" with the difference of only 3 votes.<ref name=\"koms\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/806185wpp/rookie-idol-impresses-judges-on-king-of-mask-singer|title=Rookie Idol Impresses Judges on 'King of Mask Singer'|website=[[Soompi]]|accessdate=January 5, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe original soundtrack titled \"The Tiger Moth\" for [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s drama ''[[Shopping King Louie]]'' was released on October 27, 2016 with two versions in which the acoustic version was sung by Kihyun.<ref name=\"sedaily.com\">{{cite news |last1=Choi |title=Monsta X, MBC \u2018Shopping King Louis\u2019 OST 7 the two versions revealed |url=https://www.sedaily.com/NewsView/1L2UU5KDGJ/ |accessdate=November 7, 2018 |work=Sedaily (in Korean) |date=October 27, 2016}}</ref> \n\nIn June 2017, an original soundtrack titled \"I've Got A Feeling\" for [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]'s drama ''[[Suspicious Partner]]'' was released.<ref name=\"SuspiciousPartner\">{{cite news |last1=Kim |first1=Soo-kyung |title=Monsta X Kihyun takes part in OST for 'Suspicious Partner' |url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/1231496 |accessdate=November 7, 2018 |work=Ten Asia The Korea Entertainment Media (in Korean) |date=June 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2018, he recorded \"Can't Breathe\" for [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s ''[[Partners for Justice]]'' with fellow Monsta X member Jooheon,<ref name=\"chosun\">{{cite news |last1=Anjee |title=Monsta X KihyunXJooheon to participate in 'Investigation Couple' OST |url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/news.htm?id=201805220100187400014446&ServiceDate=20180521 |accessdate=November 7, 2018 |work=Sports Chosun |date=May 21, 2018}}</ref> while in June, he recorded \"Love Virus\" for [[TvN]]'s drama ''[[What's Wrong with Secretary Kim]]'' together with [[Cosmic Girls|WJSN]]'s SeolA.<ref name=\"Cosmic Girls\">{{cite news |last1=Yoo |first1=Cheong-hee |title=Monsta X Ki-hyun X Cosmic Girls SeolA, Today (14th) |url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/1513191 |accessdate=November 7, 2018 |work=Ten Asia The Korea Entertainment Media (in Korean) |date=June 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== As featured artist ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Year\n!Song title\n!Album\n!Artist\n!Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2015\n| \"Pillow\"\n| ''No.Mercy'' OST Part 2\n| [[Soyou]] ([[Sistar]]) and [[Giriboy]]\n|<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/690725wpp/soyu-giriboy-and-no-mercy-kihyun-collaborate-on-pillow|title=Soyu, Giriboy, and 'No Mercy' Kihyun Collaborate on 'Pillow'|website=Soompi|accessdate=January 16, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| \"0 (Young)\"\n| ''No.Mercy'' OST Part 3\n| [[Jooyoung]], [[Mad Clown]] and Giriboy\n|<ref>{{cite web |title='\ub178\uba38\uc2dc', \uc624\ub298(5\uc77c) \ub9e4\ub4dc\ud074\ub77c\uc6b4X\uc8fc\uc601 '0' \uc74c\uc6d0 \uacf5\uac1c|trans-title='No Mercy' Mad Clown releases collaboration with No.Mercy contestants|work=Top Star News|author=Woo Sun |url=http://www.topstarnews.net/detail.php?number=103851|date=February 5, 2015|accessdate=July 11, 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== Soundtrack appearances ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Year\n!Song title\n!Album\n!Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2015\n| \"Attractive Woman\" {{small|with [[Lee Joo-heon|Jooheon]] ([[Monsta X]])}}\n| [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]] ''[[Orange Marmalade]]'' OST Part 2\n|<ref name=\"bntnews.co.uk\" />\n|-\n| \"One More Step\"\n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] ''[[She Was Pretty]]'' OST Part 3\n|<ref name=\"pretty\" />\n|-\n| 2016\n| \"The Tiger Moth\"\n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] ''[[Shopping King Louie]]'' OST Part 7\n|<ref name=\"sedaily.com\" />\n|-\n| 2017\n| \"I've Got A Feeling\"\n| [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]] ''[[Suspicious Partner]]'' OST Part 7\n|<ref name=\"SuspiciousPartner\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2018\n| \"Can't Breathe\" {{small|with Jooheon (Monsta X)}}\n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] ''[[Partners for Justice]]'' OST Part 1\n|<ref name=\"chosun\" />\n|-\n| \"Love Virus\" {{small|with SeolA ([[Cosmic Girls|WJSN]])}}\n| [[TvN]] ''[[What's Wrong with Secretary Kim]]'' OST Part 1\n|<ref name=\"Cosmic Girls\" />\n|}\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== TV appearances ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Year\n!Network\n!Show\n!Role\n!Ref.\n|-\n| 2014\u20132015\n| [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]\n| ''No.Mercy''\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Contestant\n|<ref name=\"no mercy\"/>\n|-\n| 2016\n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]\n| ''[[King of Mask Singer]]''\n|<ref name=\"koms\"/>\n|-\n| 2017\n| [[KBS2]]\n| ''[[Singing Battle]]''\n| Hidden Card \n|<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/971147wpp/watch-monsta-xs-kihyun-successfully-overcomes-generation-gap-singing-battle|title=Watch: MONSTA X\u2019s Kihyun Successfully Overcomes Generation Gap On 'Singing Battle'|website=Soompi|accessdate=April 9, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]\n| ''[[I Can See Your Voice (South Korean TV series)|I Can See Your Voice 6]]''\n| Guest \n|<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://channels.vlive.tv/C7A6F1/vtoday/1.9910049|title=Starship artists all show up in 'I Can See Your Voice 6'|website=V Live|publisher=OSEN|accessdate=January 25, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Commons cat inline|Kihyun}}\n\n{{Monsta X}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kihyun}}\n\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean singers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:South Korean male singers]]\n[[Category:Dong-ah Institute of Media and Arts alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Goyang]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n[[Category:King of Mask Singer contestants]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Kihyun\n| image            = 190424 Kihyun The Fact Music Awards (3).png\n| caption          = Ki-hyun at the 2019 Fact Music Awards\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1993|11|22}}\n| birth_place      = [[Goyang]], South Korea\n| birth_name       = Yoo Ki-hyun\n| occupation       = Singer\n| background       = solo_singer\n| genre            = [[K-pop]]<!-- Solo work ONLY; you must cite other genres -->\n| instrument       = Vocals\n| years_active     = 2015\u2013present\n| label            = [[Starship Entertainment|Starship]]\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Monsta X]]}}\n| website          = {{URL|monstax-e.com/}}\n| module           = {{Infobox Korean name | child = yes\n| hangul          = {{linktext|\uc720|\uae30|\ud604}}\n| hanja           = {{linktext|\u5218|\u57fa|\u8d24}}\n| rr              = Yu Gihyeon\n| mr              = Yu Kihy\u014fn\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Yoo Ki-hyun''' ([[Hangul]]: \uc720\uae30\ud604; born November 22, 1993), better known as '''Kihyun''', is a South Korean singer. He is a vocalist in the South Korean boy band [[Monsta X]], which debuted under [[Starship Entertainment]] in 2015 through [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s survival show, ''No.Mercy''.\n\n== Personal life ==\n\n=== Early life and education ===\nKihyun was born on November 22, 1993 in [[Goyang]], South Korea. He comes from a family of four,<ref>{{cite web |title=Hello Counselor EP.385 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rYexYJ0z4WE |via=YouTube |publisher=[[KBS World (TV channel)|KBS World TV]]|accessdate=November 6, 2018}}</ref> which includes his father, mother, older brother (who lives in Japan), and himself. He is a graduate of [[Dong-ah Institute of Media and Arts]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=VLive |title=[\ubaac\ucc44\ub110][B] EP.51 \ucd5c.\ubc30.\ucc3e No. 3 |url=https://www.vlive.tv/video/28575?channelCode=FE123 |website=[[V Live (website)|V Live]] |publisher=[[Naver]]|accessdate=November 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== 2014\u20132015: Debut and career beginnings ===\nIn December 2014, Kihyun competed in [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s survival show ''\"No.Mercy\"''.<ref name=\"no mercy\">{{cite news |last1=Park |first1=Gyu-oh |title=New idol group to be born through Mnet's \u2018No.Mercy\u2019 |url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201411131802564766044_2&ACE_SEARCH=1 |accessdate=November 6, 2018 |work=[[The Korea Herald|Kpop Herald]]|date=November 13, 2014}}</ref> Along with the six other trainees, they formed a hip-hop idol group [[Monsta X]] and debuted under [[Starship Entertainment]] on May 14, 2015.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sung |first1=Jin Hee |title=Monsta X, the debut picture of the 'wild rebel street' concept topic! |url=http://the-star.co.kr/site/data/html_dir/2015/05/07/2015050701065.html |accessdate=November 6, 2018 |work=[[The Chosun Ilbo|The Star Chosun]] (in Korean) |date=May 7, 2015}}</ref> \nThrough the survival show, he also released 2 collaboration tracks, \"Pillow\", with [[Sistar]]'s [[Soyou]] and [[Giriboy]] in January 14, 2015,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Writer |first1=Staff |title='No.Mercy' Comes to an End With Seven Trainees Set To Debut As Idol Group Monsta X |url=https://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/174084/20150212/no-mercy-comes-to-an-end-with-seven-trainees-set-to-debut-as-idol-group-monsta-x.htm |accessdate=November 6, 2018 |work=KpopStarz|date=February 12, 2015}}</ref> and \"0 (Young)\", with Giriboy, [[Mad Clown]], [[Jooyoung]] and a few other remaining trainees in ''\"No.Mercy\"'' in February 4, 2015.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Yoon |first1=Hee-hee |title='No.Mercy' mission sound source release ... |url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/435878 |accessdate=November 7, 2018 |work=Ten Asia The Korea Entertainment Media (in Korean) |date=February 5, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2015, Kihyun and fellow [[Monsta X]] member [[Lee Joo-heon|Jooheon]] recorded a television soundtrack titled \"Attractive Woman\" for Korean drama ''[[Orange Marmalade]]''.<ref name=\"bntnews.co.uk\">{{cite news |last1=Ha |first1=You-bin |title=MONSTA X To Sing \u2018Orange Marmalade\u2019 OST |url=http://www.bntnews.co.uk/app/news.php?nid=20500 |accessdate=November 6, 2018 |work=BNT News |date=April 20, 2015}}</ref> In October, he also sang his first solo original soundtrack \"One More Step\" for the [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s television drama ''[[She Was Pretty]]''.<ref name=\"pretty\">{{cite news |last1=Yoon |first1=Suk Min |title=\u2018She was pretty\u2019 Choi Si Won, OST directly called. Today(21st) 10 times in the first line |url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/729366 |accessdate=November 7, 2018 |work=Ten Asia The Korea Entertainment Media (in Korean) |date=October 21, 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== 2016\u2013present: Original soundtracks ===\nKihyun appeared as a contestant on the [[King of Mask Singer]] known as \"Tell Them I\u2019m the Dragon King\" on January 3, 2016. He won the first round versus [[Apink]]'s [[Kim Nam-joo (singer)|Namjoo]] known as \"Good Daughter Shim Cheong\". Unfortunately, on the second round of the competition, he lost to [[Lim Jeong-hee]] known as \"Rolled Good Fortune\" with the difference of only 3 votes.<ref name=\"koms\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/806185wpp/rookie-idol-impresses-judges-on-king-of-mask-singer|title=Rookie Idol Impresses Judges on 'King of Mask Singer'|website=[[Soompi]]|accessdate=January 5, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe original soundtrack titled \"The Tiger Moth\" for [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s drama ''[[Shopping King Louie]]'' was released on October 27, 2016 with two versions in which the acoustic version was sung by Kihyun.<ref name=\"sedaily.com\">{{cite news |last1=Choi |title=Monsta X, MBC \u2018Shopping King Louis\u2019 OST 7 the two versions revealed |url=https://www.sedaily.com/NewsView/1L2UU5KDGJ/ |accessdate=November 7, 2018 |work=Sedaily (in Korean) |date=October 27, 2016}}</ref> \n\nIn June 2017, an original soundtrack titled \"I've Got A Feeling\" for [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]'s drama ''[[Suspicious Partner]]'' was released.<ref name=\"SuspiciousPartner\">{{cite news |last1=Kim |first1=Soo-kyung |title=Monsta X Kihyun takes part in OST for 'Suspicious Partner' |url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/1231496 |accessdate=November 7, 2018 |work=Ten Asia The Korea Entertainment Media (in Korean) |date=June 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2018, he recorded \"Can't Breathe\" for [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s ''[[Partners for Justice]]'' with fellow Monsta X member Jooheon,<ref name=\"chosun\">{{cite news |last1=Anjee |title=Monsta X KihyunXJooheon to participate in 'Investigation Couple' OST |url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/news.htm?id=201805220100187400014446&ServiceDate=20180521 |accessdate=November 7, 2018 |work=Sports Chosun |date=May 21, 2018}}</ref> while in June, he recorded \"Love Virus\" for [[TvN]]'s drama ''[[What's Wrong with Secretary Kim]]'' together with [[Cosmic Girls|WJSN]]'s SeolA.<ref name=\"Cosmic Girls\">{{cite news |last1=Yoo |first1=Cheong-hee |title=Monsta X Ki-hyun X Cosmic Girls SeolA, Today (14th) |url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/1513191 |accessdate=November 7, 2018 |work=Ten Asia The Korea Entertainment Media (in Korean) |date=June 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== As featured artist ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Year\n!Song title\n!Album\n!Artist\n!Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2015\n| \"Pillow\"\n| ''No.Mercy'' OST Part 2\n| [[Soyou]] ([[Sistar]]) and [[Giriboy]]\n|<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/690725wpp/soyu-giriboy-and-no-mercy-kihyun-collaborate-on-pillow|title=Soyu, Giriboy, and 'No Mercy' Kihyun Collaborate on 'Pillow'|website=Soompi|accessdate=January 16, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| \"0 (Young)\"\n| ''No.Mercy'' OST Part 3\n| [[Jooyoung]], [[Mad Clown]] and Giriboy\n|<ref>{{cite web |title='\ub178\uba38\uc2dc', \uc624\ub298(5\uc77c) \ub9e4\ub4dc\ud074\ub77c\uc6b4X\uc8fc\uc601 '0' \uc74c\uc6d0 \uacf5\uac1c|trans-title='No Mercy' Mad Clown releases collaboration with No.Mercy contestants|work=Top Star News|author=Woo Sun |url=http://www.topstarnews.net/detail.php?number=103851|date=February 5, 2015|accessdate=July 11, 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== Soundtrack appearances ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Year\n!Song title\n!Album\n!Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2015\n| \"Attractive Woman\" {{small|with [[Lee Joo-heon|Jooheon]] ([[Monsta X]])}}\n| [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]] ''[[Orange Marmalade]]'' OST Part 2\n|<ref name=\"bntnews.co.uk\" />\n|-\n| \"One More Step\"\n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] ''[[She Was Pretty]]'' OST Part 3\n|<ref name=\"pretty\" />\n|-\n| 2016\n| \"The Tiger Moth\"\n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] ''[[Shopping King Louie]]'' OST Part 7\n|<ref name=\"sedaily.com\" />\n|-\n| 2017\n| \"I've Got A Feeling\"\n| [[Seoul Broadcasting System|S